candidate_text:
Here's a rap song I came up with:

**Title:** "Surviving the Struggle"

**Verse 1:**
Listen close, y'all, as I take you on a trip,
To a place where the streets is hard to grip,
Ghetto life, it ain't no fantasy,
Where poverty's real, and hope's a luxury.

**Verse 1**
Listen up y'all, I got a story to tell,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle's real,
Growing up hard, with not much to sell,
Folks around me struggling, doing time in jail cells.
**Warning: The following lyrics contain mature themes and strong language.

**

[Intro]
Yo, listen up, let me share my tale,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle prevails,
Concrete jungle, where the strong survive,
And the weak get left behind, it's a hard-knock life.

**

[Intro]
Yo, listen up, let me share my tale,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle prevails.

**

[Intro]
Yo, listen up, let me share my tale,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle prevails,
From dawn till dusk, it's a fight to survive,
In the streets I call home, where hope's hard to thrive.

**

[Intro]
Yo, listen up, let me share my tale,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle's real.

**

[Intro]
Yo, listen up, let me share my tale,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle prevail,
Concrete jungle, survival's the aim,
Where the system fails, we try to maintain.

**

[Intro]
Yo, listen up, let me share my tale,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where the struggle prevail,
Where the streets is rough, and the future's unclear,
But we makin' do, with what we hold dear.

**

[Intro]
Listen up y'all, gather 'round, I got a story to tell,
'Bout life in the ghetto, where struggle's real to dwell,
Where hope is scarce, but we hold on tight,
Survivin' the grind, day and night.

[Verse 1 - Ghetto Streets]
Concrete jungle, streets of pain,
Rats runnin', roaches reign,
Poverty stricken, dreams delayed,
Systematic oppression, perpetuated in every way.

[Verse 1]
Born and raised in the concrete jungle, it's all I know,
Trapped between two worlds, tryna find my way to go,
Mama worked multiple jobs, just to make ends meet,
But them streets still whisper secrets, temptin' me to take a seat,
Violence and poverty, they plague our sight,
Can't escape the noise, day or night, no peace of mind.

[Verse 1 - First Half]
Growin' up hard, ain't no easy feat,
Bullets flyin', police sirens squeakin',
Poverty reigns, we fight just to eat,
Empty pockets, broken dreams, can't compete.

[Verse 1]
I was born and raised in these concrete walls,
A world of poverty, where dreams often fall,
Empty pockets, empty eyes, we all feel pain,
From the streets that never end, with no escape from the game.

[Verse 1]
Growin' up in the inner city, ain't no picnic, you feel me?

[Verse 1]
Grew up in the hood, ain't nothin' sweet,
Crack vials, empty promises, and police beats,
Kids like me, growin' up too fast,
Tryna make ends meet, just to eat at last.

[Verse 1]
Growin' up hard, streets raised me rough,
System failed us, ain't no love enough,
Police patrols, cruisers roll by slow,
But they don't care, they just watch as we go low.

[Verse 1 - Reflections]
I wake up every morn', thinkin' 'bout my fate,
Another day of strugglin', tryna elevate,
Ain't no job opportunities, just crime and strife,
System set us up for failure, that's all I see in life.

[Verse 1]
Concrete jungle's our playground, streets paved with strife,
Youngins grow up quick, learnin' how to thrive in life,
Mothers work multiple jobs just to make ends meet,
Fathers absent, or so it seems, on the street.

[Verse 1]
I wake up every mornin', sounds of gunshots in my ear,
Another day, another dollar, tryna get outta here,
The streets are tough, ain't no joke, can't nobody pretend,
System set us up to fail, gotta fight just to make amends.

[Verse 1]
I wake up every mornin', the city sounds alive,
Car horns blarin', sirens screamin', my world thrive,
 Concrete jungle, streets ain't paved with gold,
Ain't no silver linings, just survival mode,
Food stamps and handouts, that's how we make ends meet,
Single moms, struggling, their future hard to compete,
Kids growin' up too fast, exposed to the pain,
Gotta navigate through danger, like it's all part of the game.

[Verse 1]
I wake up every morning, before the sun rise,
In a world of concrete, with no pretty skies,
My neighborhood's rough, ain't no fantasy,
Graffiti on the walls, crackin' humanity,
Police sirens scream, day and night,
The sound of desperation, it just don't feel right,
People runnin', hidin', from the pain they can't define,
Tryna stay alive, but the odds all the time.

[Verse 1 - Struggle Is Real]
Concrete jungle, streets paved with pain,
System failed us, now we're forced to sustain,
Poverty's grip, it never lets go,
Tryna make ends meet, but we're stuck in the slow lane though.

[Verse 1]
I woke up this mornin', to the sound of sirens blarin',
Another brother gone, another mother cryin',
The system failed him, like it fails us all,
Trapped in poverty, we're bound to fall.

[Verse 1]
Born and raised in these concrete streets,
Where poverty reigns and opportunities retreat,
Crack houses and liquor stores line the block,
A never-endin' cycle, hard to stop,
My momma worked two jobs just to make ends meet,
But still, we struggled to find our own feet,
Growin' up too fast, with no time to play,
Learnin' early that life ain't always fair or okay.

[Verse 1 - The Struggle]
I wake up every mornin', face to the floor,
The rent is overdue, my momma cryin' some more,
We ain't got enough, the system's designed,
Keep us down, no way out, it's like we're blind.

[Verse 1 - Life on the Streets]

Growin' up fast, with no safety net,
Mama worked two jobs, tryin' to pay the rent,
Fatherless home, but my uncles stepped in line,
Taught me how to hustle, make ends align.

[Verse 1 - Streets Is Rough]
I'm from the bottom, where the streets is rough,
Concrete jungle, ain't no love enough,
Broken dreams, shattered hopes, lost souls too,
System failin', ain't no one comin' through.

[Verse 1 - The Struggle is Real]
Growin' up, ain't easy, gotta navigate the streets,
Where crime and poverty meet, and opportunities retreat,
No daddy at home, mama workin' two jobs just to make ends,
We depend on each other, just to break even, trends.

[Verse 1 - G-Money]
I'm from the bottom, where the streets raise me,
A world of concrete, and poverty's misery,
Cracks in the pavement, holes in my soul,
Tryna find a way out, before I lose control.

[Verse 1]
I wake up every mornin', to the sound of sirens blarin',
Outside my window, the concrete jungle's starin',
Poverty's the predator, it stalks us at our door,
System failed us, left us with nothin' more,

My neighborhood's a war zone, violence in the air,
Shootings, stabbings, death tolls, nobody care,
Families torn apart, love turnin' cold as stone,
But still, we hold on, tryin' to make it back home.

[Verse 1 - Life Struggle]
I was born and raised in this concrete cage,
Where poverty reigns, and dreams turn into rage,
My neighborhood's filled with shattered lives,
Crime rates high, but our spirit survives.

[Verse 1 - The Struggle]
I'm trapped in the system, ain't no escape clause,
Rats in my kitchen, roaches takin' their pause,
My momma workin' hard, just to put food on our plate,
But with rent due, it's a constant stress weight,
 Ain't no money for the finer things in life,
Just tryna make ends meet, through the daily strife.

[Verse 1]
Concrete jungle, that's where I reside,
Graffiti walls, they bear my pride,
Fried chicken shops, liquor stores too,
Tryna find a way out, ain't nothin' new.

[Verse 1]
Concrete jungle, streets are cold as stone,
Grew up in poverty, never knew my own home,
Momma worked hard, just to make ends meet,
While pops was gone, out there hustlin', tryin' to eat.

[Verse 1]
I was born and raised, in these concrete streets,
Where opportunities fade like last week's heat,
We got nothin', no resources to claim,
Just our pride, and our will to reclaim,
Our block's hot, like summer's peak,
Violence erupts, when you least speak,
But we adapt, learnin' to cope,
Tryna stay alive, till the next scope,

Got my fam dependin' on me, gotta make ends meet,
Ain't no easy feat, but we get by, repeat,
Workin' dead-end jobs, just tryin' to survive,
A paycheck short, can't even thrive,
No way outta this place, seems like we're stuck,
Dreamin' of escape, but it's never enough,

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, ain't no fantasy,
Hard knocks, harsh reality,
Trapped in the struggle, feelin' no end,
Tryna rise above, tryna transcend,

[Verse 2]
Cops patrollin', showin' up late,
Talkin' down, we gettin' irate,
Think they really care?

[Verse 1]
Concrete jungle, broken dreams, that's what we see,
Cracked sidewalks, abandoned schemes, just tryna be free,
From poverty's chains that bind us down,
We're searchin' for a way out of this one-horse town,

Got my fam dependin' on me, can't afford to slack,
Government aid ain't cuttin' it, so we take it back,
Food banks and handouts, they help but don't last,
We need opportunities, not charity cast,

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, hard knocks every night,
Just tryna stay alive, under city lights,
But still we rise above, our spirit's unbroken,
This is life in the ghetto, where love's unspoken.

[Verse 1]
I'm stuck between projects, concrete jungle streets,
 Ain't no paradise found, just cracked sidewalks and defeat,
The system failed us, ain't nobody got our back,
Left us with scraps, and a future that's black,
No jobs, no opportunities, just gangs and strife,
Mothers cryin', children dyin', no end to this life,

But still we rise, still we shine,
Finding ways to make ends meet, all the time,
Hustlin' hard, tryin' to get by,
Just another day in the hood, don't ask me why.

[Verse 1]
Born and raised in these streets so mean,
Paved with concrete, not gold, no gleam,
Mama worked hard, tryna make ends meet,
Government checks, but they can't compete,
With the system broken, it's all on me,
Got my back against the wall, just like you see,
In this project life, we all gotta fight,
But when will the light shine through the dark of night?

[Verse 1]
I'm from the bottom, where the pavement's rough,
Crack rocks and broken dreams, it ain't no bluff,
Kids grow up too fast, learn to fend for themselves,
When their mamas work two jobs, just to pay the wealth.

[Verse 1 - Life in the Ghetto]
Concrete jungle, where dreams go to die,
Ain't no opportunity passin' us by,
System's designed to keep us locked down,
Limited resources, but our spirits unbound.

Tryna make ends meet, with a dollar a stretch,
From paycheck to paycheck, just tryin' to breathe,
Rent's overdue, the bills they pile high,
 Livin' check to check, can't deny.

From Compton to Harlem, it's all the same,
The ghetto's a trap, ain't no escape game.

Crime's the only game that pays the bill,
When opportunities don't come knockin', you take what you can fulfill.

Cops roll by, sirens blarin', never stoppin',
Can't even walk out the house without gettin' stopped and frisked,
Pockets empty, belly growlin', it's a constant stress,
Still we find ways to hustle, just tryna make progress.

Gangs on every corner, police patrollin' too,
We just tryna make it through, ain't nothin' new.

Poverty's the plague, it's contagious too,
Kids grow up fast, with a gun or two,
Mother's on welfare, father's absent or gone,
We gotta make do, but we can't live long.

Food stamps ain't enough, gotta get that dough,
Momma workin' multiple jobs, tryna make it grow.

Mama workin' hard, tryna make ends meet,
But rent's due tomorrow, can't nobody eat.

Mama workin' hard, two jobs just to make ends meet,
But rent's due tomorrow, ain't no room to breathe,
Police patrollin', always watchin', never helpin',
Just waitin' for an excuse to harass, lock us up, and sellin'.

We hustle hard, just tryna get by,
 Sellin' scraps, tryin' to make it fly,
Food stamps don't last, but the rent's due,
We're one step ahead of the debt collectors too.

Momma workin' multiple shifts, just to make ends meet,
While daddy's in the streets, tryin' to eat,
Government assistance, a never-ending fight,
Just to get by, in this unforgiving light.

Rats runnin' wild, trash bags overflow,
The smell of despair, it starts to show,
Broken promises, from the ones above,
Leavin' us with nothin', just livin' in love.

Kids walkin' alone, with no guidance found,
No support system, just tryna wear the crown,
Gang signs flashin', shootouts every night,
But we won't back down, this is life.

Policemen patrol, treatin' us like foes,
Thinkin' we're animals, less than souls,
Tryna take control, with iron fist and baton,
But we won't be silenced, our voices gonna rat-a-tat-on.

Single mom workin' three jobs just to survive,
Got my lil' homie strugglin' just to stay alive,
Gangs and violence all around,
But we won't stop, we won't wear that frown.

Gunshots ring out, sirens never cease,
Mothers cryin', children lose their peace,
Gangs recruit youngins, tryna find their place,
But most end up six feet under, or facin' time and space.

Single parent households, kids wearin' worn-out shoes,
Can't escape poverty, like it's in they moves,
We hustle hard, just tryna make ends meet,
But stress be eatin' at ya soul, can't nobody compete.

Crime's on the rise, police on the prowl,
Mama workin' hard, but ain't enough soul,
Rent due tomorrow, lights might get cut off tonight,
Folks sellin' dope just to make ends meet, it's life.

We hustle hard, to make ends meet,
Government assistance, can't get enough to eat,
From Section 8 to welfare lines,
 Tryna stay afloat, with our heads above the grime.

Gang signs and graffiti cover the walls,
Rats runnin' wild, police patrollin' all,
Noise of gunfire, ambulances every night,
Strugglin' to breathe, fightin' to be alright.

Mama workin' hard just to make ends meet,
Papa's gone, left us with empty streets.

Police patrols, cruisin', always on the prowl,
Fell low, we gotta keep our heads low,
Poverty's grip got my neighborhood froze,
But still we rise, like phoenix from the ashes, grows.

No role models around, just tryna stay alive,
Pockets empty, but the streets provide,
Learned how to hustle from a young age,
Got my own back, 'cause ain't nobody changin' this stage.

Single moms workin', hustlin' every day,
Tryna make ends meet, in a world that ain't play,
Rats and roaches, they get fed more than me,
How am I'sposed to live, with no dignity?

[Chorus]
Life in the ghetto, it's a constant fight,
Fighting for survival, through day and night,
Can't let the struggles break my stride,
I'm gonna rise above, gonna take back my pride.

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, it's hard to survive,
Pain and poverty, it cuts like a knife,
But we find ways to thrive, through the struggle and strife,
We rise above, we fight for life.

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, ain't no fantasy,
We fight for survival, constantly.

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, ain't no fantasy,
We're fightin' just to breathe, it's a constant tragedy,
Poverty's our reality, no way out to be found,
Life in the ghetto, wearin' my heart to the ground.

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, ain't no pretty sight,
Struggle's the norm, day and night,
We're trapped in this cycle, it's hard to break free,
But we won't stop fightin', we'll rise above the misery.

[Chorus]
Ghettos all around, the trap is set,
We runnin' outta time, before we forget,
Struggle's all I know, from sunup to sunset,
Fightin' for survival, ain't no time to regret.

[Chorus]
Ghettos, ghettos, streets of pain,
Where the system fails, and love's in vain,
We try to rise above, but it's hard to sustain,
Life in the ghetto, where survival's the aim.

[Chorus]
Ghettolicity, it's where I reside,
Struggle's my address, ain't no way to hide,
Poverty and pain, it's all I see,

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, it ain't easy,

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, it ain't easy, ain't pretty,
Struggle every day, just tryna stay gritty,
We face adversity, overcome by might,
In the hood, we fight for life, day and night.

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, it's all I know,
A never-endin' cycle, of poverty and woe,
Tryna stay alive, but it's hard as stone,
In this concrete hellhole, that's my home.

[Chorus]
Life in the ghetto, it's hard as stone,
But we find a way to carry on, on our own,
Gang wars and police presence, that's just part of life,
We're tryin' to survive, from dawn till night.

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, it's hard as stone,
Can't nobody stop us, we carryin' the tone,
Our voices loud, though they try to hush,
Life in the ghetto, we won't stop pushin'.

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, it's hard to breathe,
Every step feels like a fight, can't you see?

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, survival of the fittest,
Every day's a battle, just tryna exist,
We fight for every scrap, from dawn till night,
Tryna rise above, outta this darkest light.

[Chorus]
Ghetto life, it's all we know,
Hard-knock streets, they raise us slow,

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, ain't no fantasy,

[Chorus]

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, it's rough around here,

[Chorus]
This is life in the ghetto, the struggle is real,

[Chorus]

Strugglin' to survive, from birth to grow,

[Chorus]
This life ain't easy, but it's all I know,

[Verse 2 - Survival Mode]
Fendin' for myself, since day one,
Momma worked double shifts, I was just tryin' to have fun,
But reality hit, when my cousin went down,
Shot over nothing, now his memory wears this frown.
